The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 24 January is 34,036 (3,939.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 19 January, there were 3,685 new confirmed cases (426.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 12 January, there were 4,807 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (1,122 fewer cases).
